[block=center][size=18]About[/size][/block]
Boardball is a no fluff league. Coaches are players here. Teams are sets here. Players are stones here.

The aim of boardball is to move the game of orcs and lizardmen towards the seriosness of classic boardgames such as chess and go by removing the fluff completely and by providing a balanced environment which still lets enough space for players to compile their game sets with much freedom and to react on the builds of their opponents. Design and the term stone was in fact taken from go. People who were only warded off by the fantasy fluff should give boardball a try.

A player have a single dedicated set at a time. That set consists of base stones and special stones. Players have the same base sets but their set of special stones may differ. There are two kinds of special stones: extra and premium stones. Extra stones are introduced sometimes and everybody gets them. Premium stones are introduced on various events and will be added as a reward and thus will be not available for everyone.

Each player has fourteen base stones and can take one or two additional special stones to each game. The player can allocate 9 normal and 5 double skills to the base stones per tournament round. A stone may have seven skills maximum. Special stones have their fixed skills which can not be changed.

For each game the player gets three Re-rolls and 100k gold for inducements which can be used to buy regular inducements or – more importantly – one or two special stones.

Only a single tournament is held at a time. Once it is done then the application period – usually a week or two – of the next tournament will be officially announced along with its format, deadline and other information. Players have to apply to each tournament separately like for the official FUMBBL tournaments. There is no obligation in participation or activity. If the number of applicants are less than four then the tournament gets dropped and after a short break a new application period will be announced. Knockout tournaments will always start with power of two number of players and with application time as insertion order.

Stone sets are not progressing and the base set could be assembled in a common way only. Team options has to be filled up completely to get accepted into a tournament. The required amount of skills to get allocated depends of the expected number of rounds (skills = 14 × rounds) of the upcoming tournament. Creating a set is fast but allocating the skills is usually not. Once in a draw, it is worth to note the skills of the next opponent and decide about the special stones to be taken to the game.

